Tasha Smith & Keith Douglas OUT And ABOUT In LA + Ne-Yo's "R.E.D." Disc Gets September 18th RELEASE DATE!  
Jul 12 | by _YBF




Tasha Smith and her gorgeous husband, businessman Keith Douglas, were spotted out and about in LA yesterday.  See their pics inside and find out when Ne-Yo's next CD drops.
 

 Actress Tasha Smith and her husband, businessman/author Keith Douglas were spotted at a Starbucks in Los Angeles yesterday.


 Tasha is on break from filming 'Tyler Perry's For Better or Worse', which returns on Friday, July 13th at 9 pm ET/PT on TBS.


 Also, Tasha and her husband recently launched their own unisex fragrance, 'Us'.
 
 
 
And in music news......

Ne-Yo and Motown Records have announced that the singer's next disc, R.E.D. (Realizing Every Dream) will hit stores Sept. 18.
The title, said Ne-Yo, “came from me stepping outside myself, looking at my life as it is today and realizing that every dream I’ve had from the day I decided I wanted to do music, every dream that I’ve had from then til now, I’m definitely on the way to realizing it.” 
The album will feature production work from Phat Boize, Salaam Remi, and a cameo from Fabolous.  And Ne-Yo also dedicated "Alone With You" to his two-year old daughter Maddy (Madilyn Grace) who upon being brought home from the hospital as a newborn, cried and cried until this song was randomly played.

Will you get it?
 
Photos via XID/Premiere/FAMEFLYNET




