				Tasha Smith reportedly ordered to stay 2 yards away from husband for his protection			



 
 by 
thegrio

 | 

November 7, 2014 at 8:14 AM


Filed in: Entertainment 






























Actress Tasha Smith and Keith Douglas attend the New York Premiere of 'Addicted' at Regal Union Square on October 8, 2014, in New York City. (Photo by Ilya S. Savenok/Getty Images) 




Actress Tasha Smith and her husband Keith Douglas live in the same house, but they can’t get too close, according to a new court order.
Tasha must reportedly stay two yards away from Douglas when they’re home together and 100 yards away when they’re not.
Douglas claims the Why Did I Get Married star has threatened him on multiple occasions, sometimes even in front of the children. The TMZ report claims Douglas once feared falling asleep because of what Smith “might do.”
Watch: Tasha Smith Tells TheGrio: Don’t ditch your cheating man ‘over one piece of booty’
Your browser does not support iframes.
The report also claims Smith’s ‘threats’ are often accompanied by alcoholic rages.
The judge who heard Douglas’ case did not want to force Smith to leave the home until after a hearing, so the restraining order requires a minimum of two yards distance when they are in the house.
Someone call Tyler Perry – things are getting out of control.








 




 

 






